    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-28T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.00/636: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-28T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Also attention Mr. Worley.</p>
                <p>Your numbers 19, 20, 22, and 23.<note n="47" xml:id="d104fn47">Only no. 23
                        printed, <ref target="#pg_119">p. 119</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You are instructed to call, accompanied by Worley, on President of Liberia and
                    say that this Government desires to know whether it is the intention of the
                    Liberian Government to continue to pursue and sanction the methods outlined in
                    your telegrams, thus ignoring the friendly advices of the United States and the
                    principles laid down in the Reform Program of 1917.<note n="48"
                        xml:id="d104fn48">See <ref target="frus1917#pg_877">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, p. 877</ref>.</note> A
                    clear and unambiguous statement from the President is considered imperative at
                    this time before further steps under the loan arrangement are taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
